","Area 7","Area 8"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Epremotor cortex and supplementary motor area are located in Brodmann area 6\u003C/strong\u003E. This area is involved in motor planning and coordination of complex movements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArea 4\u003C/strong\u003E contains the primary motor cortex, responsible for direct execution of voluntary movements\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArea 5\u003C/strong\u003E is located in the superior parietal lobule and is involved in somatosensory association\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArea 7\u003C/strong\u003E is also in the parietal lobe and plays a role in visuo-motor coordination\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArea 8\u003C/strong\u003E contains the frontal eye fields and is involved in control of eye movements\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EArea 6 is anterior to the primary motor cortex (area 4) and plays a crucial role in planning and preparing motor actions before they are executed by the primary motor cortex.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Brodmann area 6 contains both the premotor cortex and supplementary motor area.","The primary motor cortex is located in Brodmann area 4.","Brodmann areas 5 and 7 are part of the parietal lobe, while area 8 contains the frontal eye fields."],"references":["Alan AF, Ennabe M, Wessel B, Klassen BT, Miller K. Anatomical Parcellations of Brodmann\u0027s Areas 4 and 6: A Study on Cortical Thickness for Improved Neurosurgical Planning. Cureus. 2023 Jul 2;15(7):e41280. doi: 10.7759/cureus.41280. PMID: 37405129; PMCID: PMC10315162.","Omrani M, Kaufman MT, Hatsopoulos NG, Cheney PD. Perspectives on classical controversies about the motor cortex. J Neurophysiol. 2017 Sep 1;118(3):1828-1848. doi: 10.1152/jn.00795.2016. Epub 2017 Jun 14. PMID: 28615340; PMCID: PMC5599665.","Yip DW, Awosika AO, Lui F. Physiology, Motor Cortical. 2024 Jun 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31194345.","Hall, J. E., \u0026 Hall, M. E. (2020). Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology E-Book: Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Singh, V. (2024).\u00a0Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50986"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16514"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50986","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50986"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-26T15:28:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-26T23:10:22+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9205"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65547"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{